# 07_substrate_manifest — what the script substrate supports today.
#
# This file documents the verb/query surface of every curvz::widgets
# wrapper type lifted into the substrate during s187 m1. Not a test —
# nothing to assert against — but a runnable manifest: read the
# comments below; uncomment any line and Run to see if it dispatches.
#
# Today (s187 m2 close-out) the only registered wrapper instance is
# `tool.node` (a ToggleButton). The other six wrapper types compile in
# but have no construction sites yet. The funnel migration in a
# following session wires up the toolbar (~22 tool buttons), at which
# point the abbrev-keyed tests below start dispatching against real
# widgets.
#
# ── ToggleButton ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   verbs:    click            (signal-bound, uses synchronizer)
#             set <bool>       (synchronous setter)
#   queries:  active           → Bool
#             label            → String
#   emits:    toggled <bool>
#
# Live example (uncomment to run):
#   # tool.node click
#   # assert tool.node active == true
#
# ── Button ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   verbs:    click            (signal-bound, uses synchronizer)
#   queries:  label            → String
#   emits:    clicked
#
# ── Entry ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   verbs:    set "<text>"     (synchronous setter)
#             clear            (same as set "")
#   queries:  text             → String
#   emits:    changed <text>
#
# ── SpinButton ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   verbs:    set <number>     (synchronous setter)
#             step <int>       (positive forward, negative backward)
#   queries:  value            → Double
#             min              → Double
#             max              → Double
#   emits:    value_changed <number>
#
# ── Scale ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   verbs:    set <number>     (synchronous setter)
#   queries:  value            → Double
#             min              → Double
#             max              → Double
#   emits:    value_changed <number>
#
# ── DropDown ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   verbs:    set <int>        (zero-based index)
#             pick "<text>"    (lookup by visible text)
#   queries:  selected         → Int
#             text             → String (text of selected entry)
#             count            → Int (number of options)
#   emits:    selected <int>
#
# ── CheckButton ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   verbs:    click            (toggles via synchronous set_active)
#             set <bool>       (synchronous setter)
#   queries:  active           → Bool
#             label            → String
#   emits:    toggled <bool>
#
# ── Built-in listener verbs ─────────────────────────────────────────
#   list                                 print registered objects + long_names
#   get <object> <property>              query, echo
#   assert <object> <property> == <lit>  query, compare
#   subscribe                            start logging emit events
#   sleep <ms>                           yield to main loop
#   quit                                 end the script early
#
# Run this file to confirm the listener is alive — it'll just print
# the file content as comments (every line starts with #) and a
# trivial summary.

# end of manifest
